UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Coloplast Intermittent Catheter for Men (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The Coloplast Intermittent Catheter for Men (Multi-Sizes) is an advanced solution designed to provide an optimized intermittent catheterization experience. Made from high-quality medical PVC, this device offers exceptional biocompatibility, thereby minimizing the risk of tissue reaction. The ethylene oxide (EO) sterilization process ensures product purity, eliminating all potential contaminants and ensuring maximum safety with each use.</p><p>Equipped with a hydrophilic tip, this catheter offers smoother and atraumatic insertion, reducing discomfort for the patient. The available sizes - 14 Fr, 16 Fr, 18 Fr - allow for optimal adaptation according to the specific clinical needs of patients. Each catheter is individually packaged in a sterile manner, thus ensuring protection against environmental pathogens and maintaining product integrity until use.</p><p>In compliance with CE standards, this catheter meets the strict safety and efficacy criteria required in modern clinical environments. The ergonomic design and high-quality materials used in the manufacture of the Coloplast Intermittent Catheter for Men demonstrate Coloplast''s uncompromising commitment to innovation and clinical excellence.</p><table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200"><thead class="bg-gray-50"><tr><th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Specification</th><th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Details</th></tr></thead><tbody class="bg-white divide-y divide-gray-200"><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Material</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Medical PVC</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Sterilization</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Ethylene Oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Compliance</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">CE</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Clinical Use</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Single use</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Features</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Hydrophilic tip, sizes 14 Fr, 16 Fr, 18 Fr, sterile individual packaging</td></tr></tbody></table><p>This medical device is designed with high clinical quality materials. Key technical features: <strong>Material</strong>: Soft PVC with hydrophilic PVP coating. <strong>Lubrication</strong>: Pre-lubricated, ready to use after immersion in water. <strong>Design</strong>: Fire-polished eyes for atraumatic insertion. <strong>Clinical Use</strong>: Self-intermittent catheterization (SIC), prevention of urethral micro-traumas. </p>' WHERE id = 522;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Lumbar Puncture Needle (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The Lumbar Puncture Needle (Multi-Sizes) is designed to meet the rigorous demands of modern clinical practices. Made from 304 stainless steel, it ensures superior biocompatibility while offering exceptional durability for intensive use. This material perfectly meets high safety standards, thus minimizing the risks of nosocomial infections and adverse reactions.</p>

<p>Sterilized with ethylene oxide (EO), this needle guarantees impeccable sterility, essential for medical practices where patient safety is paramount. With its varied sizes from 18G to 25G, it allows maximum adaptability to meet the specific needs of each procedure.</p>

<p>This needle is distinguished by its atraumatic bevel, a key feature aimed at reducing tissue trauma and improving patient comfort. Its individually sterilized packaging ensures quick and efficient preparation during urgent and critical medical procedures.</p>

