UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Combined Elbow Filter Anti-bacterial Heat and Moisture Exchanger Straight/Wet Ventilation', description_en = '<p>The Combined Elbow Filter Anti-bacterial Heat and Moisture Exchanger Straight/Ventilation-Humidifier, SKU RUS18402T, is a technological advancement in the field of clinical ventilation. Designed to meet the highest performance standards, this medical device is distinguished by its extraordinary ability to perform both bacterial filtration and humidification of respiratory air. Its medical-grade polypropylene composition ensures optimal biocompatibility, thus minimizing any risk of irritation or adverse reaction during prolonged use.</p>

<p>The product''s ergonomics have been carefully studied to ensure a non-traumatic fit to ventilation systems in demanding clinical environments. With a bacterial filtration efficiency of ≥ 99.99%, this filter is vital in clinical scenarios where the prevention of airborne infections is paramount. Each unit is sterilized by ethylene oxide, a process that ensures sterility while preserving the integrity of its materials. This device is certified compliant with CE ISO 13485 standards, ensuring its adherence to the strict safety and performance requirements of medical devices.</p>

<p>The sterile individual packaging of the product facilitates its practical and immediate use in clinical settings. With its compact dimensions – a length of 10 cm and a diameter of 2 cm – the filter easily integrates into ventilation systems, optimizing both patient comfort and clinical efficiency. This device is an ideal choice for healthcare facilities that value quality, safety, and patient-centered care.</p>

<table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
  <thead>
    <tr class="border-b">
      <th class="px-4 py-2">Specification</th>
      <th class="px-4 py-2">Details</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr class="border-b">
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Material</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Medical-grade polypropylene</td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="border-b">
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Sterilization</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Ethylene oxide (EO)</td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="border-b">
      <td class="px-4 py-2">CE / ISO Compliance</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-2">CE compliant with ISO 13485 standard</td>
    </tr>
    <tr class="border-b">
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Clinical Use</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Filtration and humidification in ventilation systems</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Features</td>
      <td class="px-4 py-2">Bacterial efficiency ≥ 99.99%</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table><p>This medical device is designed with high clinical quality materials. Key technical features: <strong>Filter Type</strong>: HMEF (Heat and Moisture Exchanger + Bacterial Filter). <strong>Efficiency (BFE/VFE)</strong>: > 99.999%. <strong>Flow Resistance</strong>: 1.5 cmH2O at 30 L/min. <strong>Dead Space</strong>: 45 ml. <strong>Water Output</strong>: 32 mg/H2O at VT 500ml. <strong>Clinical Use</strong>: Anesthesia and resuscitation (Protects the patient and the ventilator).</p>' WHERE id = 57;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Non-Powdered Latex Surgical Gloves (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The Non-Powdered Latex Surgical Gloves are designed to meet the stringent requirements of high-precision medical environments. Made from premium natural latex, these gloves offer exceptional biocompatibility, minimizing the risk of allergic reactions while ensuring optimal protection for healthcare professionals. Their ambidextrous design allows for practical and ergonomic use, fitting perfectly to each user while ensuring remarkable tactile sensation and unparalleled dexterity.</p>

<p>Equipped with CE certification, these gloves comply with the most rigorous standards for medical devices, ensuring their reliability and effectiveness in critical clinical procedures. Ethylene oxide (EO) sterilization ensures that the gloves remain perfectly sterile until use, thus guaranteeing safety for both practitioners and patients. This atraumatic approach reduces the risk of cross-contamination and protects the integrity of sterile surgical environments.</p>

<p>Available in multiple sizes, including small, medium, and large, these gloves are designed to suit a wide range of healthcare professionals, from surgical operations to patient examinations. Each box contains 100 units, optimizing storage while ensuring that practitioners always have a sufficient supply at hand. This product represents the perfect alliance between advanced technology and a constant focus on safety and clinical efficiency.</p>

