UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Coloplast Intermittent Catheter for Women (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The Coloplast Female Intermittent Catheter is designed to provide optimal comfort and safety during self-catheterization procedures. Made from high-quality medical-grade PVC, this catheter ensures high biocompatibility, thereby minimizing the risk of adverse reactions. Its ethylene oxide sterilization guarantees rigorous asepsis, essential for preventing any infection related to intermittent use.</p><p>Specifically optimized for female use, the catheter is available in various sizes, ranging from 10 cm to 20 cm, ensuring adaptability to different individual anatomies. The ergonomic design includes a hydrophilic rounded tip, promoting atraumatic and smooth insertion, reducing discomfort for the user while optimizing urinary drainage efficiency.</p><p>The CE compliance of the Coloplast Female Intermittent Catheter underscores its adherence to the strictest safety and performance standards. Designed for single use, it is individually packaged, ensuring maximum sterility until opened. This user-centered design emphasizes ease of use and cost-effectiveness, making it ideal for safe and effective clinical use.</p><table class=''min-w-full text-left text-sm''><thead><tr><th class=''px-4 py-2''>Feature</th><th class=''px-4 py-2''>Details</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Material</td><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>High-quality medical-grade PVC</td></tr><tr><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Sterilization</td><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Ethylene Oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Compliance</td><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>CE Compliant</td></tr><tr><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Clinical Use</td><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Sterile single use</td></tr><tr><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Features</td><td class=''border px-4 py-2''>Available in lengths from 10 cm to 20 cm, hydrophilic rounded tip, individual packaging</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 523;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Auricular Speculum (Greatcare) (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p><strong>Auricular Speculum (Greatcare) (Multi-Sizes)</strong> is a high-quality medical instrument designed for professional ear examination. Made from premium 304 stainless steel, this speculum offers not only exceptional durability but also optimal biocompatibility, ensuring patient safety and comfort. Its ergonomic structure aids healthcare professionals in performing ear inspections with ease and precision.</p> <p>With ethylene oxide (EO) sterilization, the Auricular Speculum ensures perfect asepsis, essential in clinical settings where infection prevention is paramount. The product is available in multiple sizes (small, medium, large), allowing for individual adaptation for each patient, enhancing user experience and minimizing trauma risks with an atraumatic rounded tip.</p> <p>This device is CE certified, reflecting its adherence to the stringent health and safety standards of the European Union. Intended for exclusive professional use in clinics or hospitals, it is individually packaged in sterile packaging, providing additional safety during storage and use. The Auricular Speculum (Greatcare) is an ideal choice for professionals seeking to optimize their clinical practices with reliable and sophisticated equipment.</p> <table class="table-fixed w-full border-separate border-spacing-2 border border-gray-300"> <thead> <tr class="bg-gray-100"> <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Material</th> <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Sterilization</th> <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Compliance</th> <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Clinical Use</th> <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Features</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr> <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">304 Stainless Steel</td> <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Ethylene Oxide (EO)</td> <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">CE certified</td> <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Professional use in clinic or hospital</td> <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Available in multiple sizes (small, medium, large), Rounded tip for optimal comfort, Individual sterile packaging</td> </tr> </tbody> </table>' WHERE id = 571;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Spinal Needle (Quincke Bevel) (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed font-light text-gray-700">The Spinal Needle (Quincke Bevel) is a premium medical device designed to offer exceptional performance and optimal safety during clinical and hospital interventions. Made from 304 stainless steel, this needle is renowned for its durability and corrosion resistance, thus ensuring undeniable <strong>biocompatibility</strong>. The Quincke-type design ensures atraumatic tissue penetration, minimizing trauma and enhancing patient comfort.</p><p class="text-lg leading-relaxed font-light text-gray-700">Intended for clinical use, this sterile single-use needle is perfect for performing lumbar punctures and other procedures requiring precise penetration. Each needle undergoes a rigorous ethylene oxide (EO) sterilization process, ensuring microbial safety and delivery in a sterile state. Its compliance with CE standards attests to its adherence to European quality standards, reinforcing its reliability among healthcare practitioners worldwide.</p><p class="text-lg leading-relaxed font-light text-gray-700">Available in multiple sizes (20G to 27G), the Spinal Needle (Quincke Bevel) offers flexibility and adaptability for various clinical needs. The Quincke bevel is designed to maximize penetration efficiency while preserving tissue integrity. The ergonomic design supports healthcare professionals in their clinical endeavors, ensuring precise and controlled actions. Designed for the demanding environments of medical and hospital centers, it represents an essential tool for specialists seeking precision and safety.</p><table class="min-w-full bg-white border border-gray-200 mt-4"><thead class="bg-gray-50"><tr><th class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 font-semibold text-gray-700 text-left">Specification</th><th class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 font-semibold text-gray-700 text-left">Details</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Material</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">304 Stainless Steel</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Sterilization</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Ethylene Oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">CE / ISO Compliance</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">CE Certification</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Clinical Use</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Clinical and hospital setting</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Features</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200 text-gray-600">Sterile, single-use, Tip type: Quincke Bevel</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 9;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Coloplast Intermittent Catheter for Children Ch.8', description_en = '<div class="max-w-lg mx-auto">
    <p class="mb-4">The Coloplast catheter for pediatric intermittent catheterization Ch.8 represents a significant advancement in ergonomics and safety for pediatric urological procedures. Specifically designed to meet the delicate needs of young patients, this catheter uses high-quality medical PVC to ensure not only biocompatibility but also optimal flexibility that minimizes the risk of irritation or trauma during use. The length of 30 cm and the Ch.8 gauge (equivalent to an outer diameter of 2.7 mm) are perfectly adjusted for infant anatomies.</p>
    <p class="mb-4">Each catheter is sterilized by ethylene oxide (EO), ensuring rigorous sterility recognized by CE standards. Intended for single use, it is individually packaged to maintain sterility and optimize the control of nosocomial infections. The ergonomic design includes a rounded atraumatic tip that facilitates gentle insertion and reduces the risk of complications during interventions.</p>
    <p class="mb-4">This medical device comes with full CE compliance, certifying that every aspect of its production, from material selection to final inspection, meets the strictest European standards of safety and efficacy. Due to its sophisticated design, this catheter represents a reliable solution for healthcare professionals, ensuring both the safety of young patients and the effectiveness of treatment.</p>
