  </tr>
</table><p>This medical device is designed with high clinical quality materials. Key technical features: <strong>Type</strong>: Corrugated, stretchable. <strong>Dead Volume</strong>: 15 ml (minimizes CO2 rebreathing). <strong>Connectivity</strong>: Standard connectors 22F/15M - 15F. <strong>Sterilization</strong>: Single-use, sterile packaging. <strong>Clinical Use</strong>: Connection between the breathing circuit and the patient tube. </p>' WHERE id = 54;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Non-Sterile Examination Gloves (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed"><strong>Non-Sterile Examination Gloves (Multi-Sizes)</strong>, SKU reference: NEO152100, offer a proven solution for clinical and hospital needs. Made from <em>nitrile</em>, a material renowned for its exceptional <strong>biocompatibility</strong> and resistance properties, these gloves provide reliable protection against a wide range of contaminants. The non-sterile nature of these gloves allows their use in non-invasive procedures where sterile contact is not required.</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">These gloves are designed to be <strong>ergonomic</strong>, ensuring optimal comfort during long periods of use. Available in multiple sizes - <em>Small, Medium, Large, and Extra Large</em> - they provide an atraumatic fit, minimizing the risk of fatigue or skin irritation. The nitrile composition gives them high puncture resistance, offering an ideal combination of protection and flexibility.</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">The gloves meet <strong>CE compliance</strong> standards, ensuring they adhere to current quality and safety standards. Packaged in boxes of 100, they are easy to store and ready for <strong>single use</strong>. Their distinct blue color allows for quick identification and reduces the risk of cross-contamination.</p>

