UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Luer Slip Syringe - 3-Part Latex-Free Syringe - 20ml', description_en = '<p>The 20 ml Luer Slip Syringe, coded under SKU: NE176520, is a highly sophisticated medical device designed to meet the rigorous demands of modern clinical and hospital environments. Developed without latex, this syringe minimizes the risk of allergic reactions, ensuring maximum biocompatibility with human tissues. Its three-part design is optimized to guarantee precise and consistent medication administration, contributing to a smooth and secure user experience for medical personnel.</p><p>Manufactured from polypropylene, a material known for its strength and transparency, this syringe offers superior ergonomics, facilitating handling even during complex procedures. Ethylene oxide (EO) sterilization ensures strict asepsis, essential for preventing nosocomial infections. Each syringe is individually packaged, thus preserving its sterile integrity until the moment of use.</p><p>Compliance with CE standards is an additional guarantee of safety and performance, attesting to the commitment to the highest quality standards. As a single-use device, it is specifically suited for various clinical interventions while ensuring operational efficiency and a high level of sanitary control. The Luer Slip connector, for its part, offers a quick and reliable connection to associated components, maximizing ease of use.</p><table class="min-w-full border-collapse">  <thead>    <tr class="border-b">      <th class="px-4 py-2">Technical Specifications</th>      <th class="px-4 py-2">Details</th>    </tr>  </thead>  <tbody>    <tr class="border-b">      <td class="px-4 py-2">Material</td>      <td class="px-4 py-2">Latex-free polypropylene</td>    </tr>    <tr class="border-b">      <td class="px-4 py-2">Sterilization</td>      <td class="px-4 py-2">Ethylene oxide (EO)</td>    </tr>    <tr class="border-b">      <td class="px-4 py-2">CE / ISO Compliance</td>      <td class="px-4 py-2">CE Certification</td>    </tr>    <tr class="border-b">      <td class="px-4 py-2">Clinical Use</td>      <td class="px-4 py-2">Single-use, professional in clinical and hospital settings</td>    </tr>    <tr class="border-b">      <td class="px-4 py-2">Features</td>      <td class="px-4 py-2">Individually packaged in a pouch, Tip type: Luer Slip</td>    </tr>  </tbody></table>' WHERE id = 561;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Essential Dental Care Kit', description_en = '<p>The <strong>Essential Dental Care Kit</strong> (SKU: KIT-DENT-001) is distinguished by its precision engineering and manufacturing with the highest quality materials. Specially designed for daily dental procedures, this kit embodies a perfect balance between functionality and clinical comfort. Each instrument is made of <em>304 Stainless Steel</em>, known for its durability and corrosion resistance, thus ensuring optimal biocompatibility with human tissues. The atraumatic design of the instruments enhances the safety and comfort profile during dental assessment and treatment procedures.</p>

<p>Our kit is meticulously sterilized using <em>ethylene oxide (EO)</em>, providing additional assurance of safety against cross-contamination. This sterilization method ensures the microbiological purity of the instruments, making them ready for immediate use. This commitment to safety is reinforced by the <strong>CE</strong> certification, demonstrating our compliance with stringent European standards for medical devices.</p>

<p>Designed for <em>single use</em>, the instruments in the Essential Dental Care Kit are individually packaged, facilitating their rapid and efficient implementation while minimizing infection risks. The 15 cm dimensions for each tool are specifically chosen for ergonomic balance, allowing precise handling and easy access to intraoral spaces for optimal care. Whether for use in a clinic or hospital settings, this kit is intended to be an indispensable tool for any dentist concerned with the quality of care provided to their patients.</p>

